"/> Ammonia is a general cleaner and degreaser - it'll do nothing
for mineral deposits (which are usually lime.)
Try these (in sequence):
1 - Buy a bottle of the &quot;concentrated&quot; vinegar in the grocery
store and pour it in full-strength. (Of course, if this bowl
is large, you'll need more than one.) Let it soak (cover
the bowl with plastic to avoid evaporation) for two or
three days. By then, the deposits should either have
melted away, or have been loosened.

2 - Lime-Away (even stronger.) Read the label directions
very carefully.

If neither of those work, you'll need to consult a glass expert
to determine if the inside of the bowl should be repolished
(which will devalue it, but at that point, it's not a problem.)

Kris

